HOW TO CREATE A NEW REPOSITORY IN THE GITHUB CLIENT

Step 1:
  Double-click on the "GitHub Desktop" icon to open the GitHub client.

Step 2:
  At the top left corner of the program window, click File > New repository...
  
Step 3:
  In the "Create a new repository" pop-up window, enter a name and short description for your depository.
  
Step 4:
  Check the box to "Initialize this repository with a README", and then click the "Create repository" button.
  
Step 5:
  Pat yourself on the back! You have successfully created a new repository using your GitHub client!
